{"word":"ναυκληρία","slug":"ναυκληρία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ναυκληρία</b></el> <el>(ναυκληρία, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ναύκληρος'><el>ναύκληρος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a seafaring life, ship-owning</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <i>a voyage</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <i>an adventure, enterprise</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a ship</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}